# AI Assistant Workspace Rules & Deploy Guide

Please follow these guidelines automatically whenever making changes to this codebase:

---

## 1. Vercel CDN Deploys (Frontend Portals Only)
* Whenever you modify files in `client-portal/`, `admin-portal/`, or `marketing-site/`, you **MUST** commit and push the changes to their respective GitHub repositories to trigger Vercel CDN builds (`client.buykori.app`, `admin.buykori.app`, `buykori.app`).
* Pushing the root repository (`full-project-` / branch `main` or `master`) is **NOT** connected to Vercel and does not trigger any deployment. It is only used as a manual code backup repository.

---

## 2. Client Portal Build & Local Static Sync
* If you edit any code in `client-portal/src/`, you **must** build the production bundle and copy it to the static fallback folder of the backend:
  1. Run `npm run build` inside `client-portal/`.
  2. Clear old assets: `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force "app\static\client-portal\assets\*"`
  3. Copy new build: `Copy-Item -Recurse -Force "client-portal\dist\*" "app\static\client-portal\"`

---

## 3. Server Deployments (DigitalOcean Droplet - Backend & Migrations)
* To deploy python backend code (`app/`), database migrations (`migrations/`), and static assets to the live DigitalOcean Droplet, you **MUST** run:
  ```powershell
  python scratch/deploy_updates.py
  ```
  from the workspace root. This syncs changes, applies PostgreSQL migrations, and restarts the web/worker services. 
* Do **NOT** assume pushing to the root `full-project-` repository deploys backend changes. Backend deployment is strictly done via this command.
